    {
      "id": "25",
      "name": "Additional Information",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "textual_research",
          "data": {
            "list": [
              {
                "audios": [],
                "desc": "<p>(The handwriting here is exquisite, to the point of seeming like some sort of printout. This doesn&#39;t look like a fortune slip...)</p><p>To be honest, we weren&#39;t the most familiar of people in the organization Alice founded. But I find that things and people around me have changed much in the many years that followed... and now, you are amongst the few I am most acquainted with.</p><p>I must confess that I did not initially understand what Alice saw in you. Being &#34;interesting&#34; was the measuring stick, said she, and being the &#34;most interesting&#34; was the only criterion for being invited to join. Later, I realized that I had only thought that I had understood your stories. That your acuity for the world&#39;s operating principles could perhaps sometimes surpass that of astrology. Sometimes, that is!</p><p>I, too, have grown old, and I do not know how long I have left. So yes, I admit that I really do miss you, just a little. Not that I would actually go over to keep you company or anything, though.</p>",
                "title": "A fortune slip"
              },
              {
                "audios": [],
                "desc": "<p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Barbeloth</span>: Are you sure you want to create this child, M, even after what I told you about his fate?</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Barbeloth</span>: He will be abandoned by his creator, and eventually...</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Andersdotter</span>: I know, B. You&#39;ve told me already. That sad story with the disappointing ending... It&#39;s what happened in the real world, isn&#39;t it?</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Andersdotter</span>: But, that&#39;s exactly why I want to change things. In a different world, his story can have a happier ending. That child... His heart is so full of love.</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Barbeloth</span>: I understand, Anya. But, know that if you give him that name, his fate in Simulanka is destined to parallel that of his real-world namesake...</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Andersdotter</span>: But, there&#39;s still a chance, right? Maybe it&#39;s a shot in the dark... But, I have to try. He deserves a better life.</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Andersdotter</span>: Although... he might need the help of others when the time comes.</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Barbeloth</span>: Alright, my dear, the choice is yours.</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Barbeloth</span>: Since you&#39;re so persistent, let me tell you a secret...</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(55, 255, 255)\">Barbeloth</span>: R&#39;s child... will one day rise from the dead.</p>",
                "title": "About Durin of Simulanka"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
